# Global Project Rules

## Null Safety
- Never use `!` to force-unwrap a nullable value without first checking it with `if`, `?.`, `??`, pattern matching, or another explicit null-safe guard.

## Comments
- Do not leave comments in source code.
- Only keep comments that are required by tooling or generated code conventions.

## Failure And Exception Boundaries
- `Failure` is the business-layer error model. Use it outside the data layer.
- `Exception` is the data-layer error model. Do not expose exceptions to domain or presentation layers.
- Catch data-layer exceptions and map them to `Failure` before returning across repository boundaries.
